image.altText: David Warner attempts a shot but the ball hits the stumps, sending the bails flying

items.synopsis: England smashes 592 runs, with Jonny Bairstow stranded on 99 not out, on day three at Old Trafford in the fourth Ashes Test. Follow live.

title.children: Australia begins rescue mission with the bat after England build massive lead

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh it's a horrible dismissal for Steve Smith. A bouncer from Wood, Smith stepped inside and hooked, feathering the ball to Bairstow behind the stumps! It's just a nothing ball that Smith should have left well alone! He's out for 17 and Australia are in a spot of bother, trailing by 178,
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SMITH IS OUT! HE'S WALKING!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Interesting session there. The Bairstow fireworks helped England to a sizable first innings lead, and then the Mark Wood thunderbolts helped bring the wicket of Usman Khawaja with Australia still trailing by 236 runs. A good final session from Australia here could go a long way to saving the Test, if we're already talking in terms of this match needing to be saved. But England could go a long way to winning there if they get things right. Intriguing stuff to come.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Tea: Australia 1-39 (Warner 17, Labuschagne 1), trail by 236

children.content: (Getty Images)
Interesting session there.
The Bairstow fireworks helped England to a sizable first innings lead, and then the Mark Wood thunderbolts helped bring the wicket of Usman Khawaja with Australia still trailing by 236 runs.
A good final session from Australia here could go a long way to saving the Test, if we're already talking in terms of this match needing to be saved.
But England could go a long way to winning there if they get things right.
Intriguing stuff to come.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Khawaja looks a bit confused but England are adamant this is out - AND HE HAS BEEN GIVEN! He fended at a wide rising ball and feathered it through to the keeper. Khawaja has reviewed after a brief chat with Warner. There's a snick though and it's out! Australia loses a review. Khawaja goes early, for 18 off 34.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: APPEAL FOR CAUGHT BEHIND! HE'S GIVEN!
